column14: \"Note\"","\"PARSEME corpora annotated for verbal multiword expressions (version 1.3)\"
column17: \"identification of verbal multi-word expressions (idioms, light-verb constructions, verb-particle constructions, inherently reflexive verbs, multi-verb constructions)\"
column20: \"Arabic, Basque, Bulgarian, Chinese, Croatian, Czech, English, French, German, Hebrew, Hindi, Hungarian, Irish, Italian, Lithuanian, Maltese, Modern Greek (1453-), Persian, Polish, Portuguese, Romanian, Serbian, Slovenian, Spanish, Swedish, Turkish \"
column21:
\"This multilingual resource contains corpora in which verbal multi-word expressions (MWEs) have been manually annotated. Verbal MWEs include idioms (let the cat out of the bag), light-verb constructions (make a decision), verb-particle constructions (give up), inherently reflexive verbs (help oneself), and multi-verb constructions (make do).#SEPThe 1.0 versions of the PARSEME corpora can be queried individually through KonText. We provide the individual links to each corpus:#SEP
  1. Parseme VMWE 1.0 – Czech
  2. Parseme VMWE 1.0 – German
  3. Parseme VMWE 1.0 – Greek
  4. Parseme VMWE 1.0 – Spanish
  5. Parseme VMWE 1.0 – Persian
  6. Parseme VMWE 1.0 – French
  7. Parseme VMWE 1.0 – Hungarian
  8. Parseme VMWE 1.0 – Italian
  9. Parseme VMWE 1.0 – Maltese
  10. Parseme VMWE 1.0 – Polish
  11. Parseme VMWE 1.0 – Portuguese
  12. Parseme VMWE 1.0 – Romanian
  13. Parseme VMWE 1.0 – Slovenian
  14. Parseme VMWE 1.0 – Swedish
  15. Parseme VMWE 1.0 – Turkish
\"
column34: \"This corpus contains Tweets. The corpus is morphosyntactically tagged following the MULTEXT-East Version 4 tagset.#SEPThe corpus is available through the concordancers KonText and noSketchEngine and for download from the CLARIN.SI repository.\"
column47: \"This corpus contains legal texts.#SEPThe corpus is available through the concordance KonText, the PML-TQ tool and for download from the LINDAT repository.\"
column56: \"mark-up of discourse phenomena enriched by the annotation of secondary connectives\"
column60: \"This corpus is a subset of the Prague Dependency Treebank 3.5.#SEPThe corpus is available through the PML-TQ tool.\"
column73: \"This corpus is an extended version of Prague Czech-English Dependency Treebank 2.0, with added mark-up of coreference. The syntactic parsing follows the PDT 2.0 styleD#SEPThe corpus is available for download from the LINDAT repository. The version without coreference annotation is available through the concordancer KonText and the PML-TQ tool.T 2.0 style.\"
column86: \"The syntactic parsing follows the Universal Dependencies schema.#SEPThe corpus is available for download from the LINDAT repository.\"
column99: \"This corpus contains the literary works of the Danish bishop N.F.S Grundtvig.#SEPThe corpus is available for download from the CLARIN-DK repository.\"
column112: \"This is a manually annotated subset of the much larger (approx.. 500 million) word) SoNaR corpus.#SEPThe corpus is available for download from the Dutch Language Institute.\"
column125: \"This corpus contains 6818 terms extracted from abstracts of computational linguistics papers.#SEPThe corpus is available for download from LINDAT and through KonText.\"
column138: \"This corpus contains literary, newspaper and biography texts.#SEPThe corpus is available for download from the Oxford Text Archive.\"

column177: \"The corpus is available for download from META-SHARE (CELR distribution).\"
column190: \"In addition to coreference, the corpus is annotated for identity and bridging relations.#SEPIn addition to coreference, the corpus is annotated for identity and bridging relations.\"
column203: \"This corpus contains texts from the domains of politics, law and travel.#SEPThis corpus is available for download from the clarin:el repository.\"
